It took a long while for me to understand that I needed to open up more and strengthen my body before this pose could work for me.  I’ve been working so hard to increase my flexibility and strength, hoping to be able to push up into wheel with ease. 
During class today, my sister-in-law spoke about fear and letting go, finding strength and going for it.  In the moment I found myself fearful and uncertain so I passed up the opportunity to attempt the pose.  When I got home I realized that I would not let fear or uncertainty get the best me.  I went for it. 
I could actually breathe and appreciate my progress, my journey. 

You’re never stuck.  Stay positive & know that you have the choice and ability to grow. 
Choose to persist. 
Choose to embrace your struggles and appreciate your growth. 🌱

